5
00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:22.300
which is really the root folder; next to that is a plus symbol.

6
00:00:22.300 --> 00:00:26.866
When you hover over it, GitHub tells you that you can create a new file here.

7
00:00:26.866 --> 00:00:30.000
However, if I wanted to, I could drill down into this folder

8
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.166
and then, under the "website/" the folder name,

9
00:00:33.166 --> 00:00:36.066
you can create a new file in this location as well.

10
00:00:36.066 --> 00:00:39.466
I'm going to create a new file at the root of this repository.

11
00:00:39.466 --> 00:00:41.933
So, I'm going to go back to the root of the repository,

12
00:00:41.933 --> 00:00:45.100
and then click on the plus mark to create a new file here.

13
00:00:45.100 --> 00:00:48.366
When creating a new file, you need to give the file a name.

14
00:00:48.366 --> 00:00:54.100
