15
00:00:54.100 --> 00:00:57.600
If you wanted to, you can get out of here by just clicking on "cancel";

16
00:00:57.600 --> 00:01:01.400
that returns us directly back to the main page of our repository.

17
00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:04.833
Let's go back into it. Now that we're back on the create new file,

18
00:01:04.833 --> 00:01:10.766
I'm going to name this file "lipsum.txt". I'm going to go to "lipsum.com",

19
00:01:10.766 --> 00:01:15.833
then copy a paragraph of lorem ipsum; copy, and then paste.

20
00:01:15.833 --> 00:01:20.633
Before we save the file, we can preview it; let's give it some reasonable breaks.

21
00:01:20.633 --> 00:01:25.133
There we go; that looks decent. Like before, once we are done

22
00:01:25.133 --> 00:01:29.566
let's scroll all the way down to the bottom of the page, and put in our commit message:

23
00:01:29.566 --> 00:01:34.233
"Create new file -- filler text". This time I'm going to decide to create a new branch,

24
00:01:34.233 --> 00:01:36.866
